Thus,

1. ‘Even now’ signifies ‘atthis present time} ‘directly,' ‘without delay‚' in such phrases as ‘the battle is even now going on,’ ‘I must leave you even now,’ and the like.

2. With a negative ‘even now' may signify ‘yet,' ‘as yet‚' ‘up to this time‚' in such phrases as ‘even now the boy cannot write,’ ‘even now I have never employed him in such.worlr.’
